@node part5 "Why did I create it?"

    I know that many other programs similar to mine already exist.
    I decided that I wanted a challenging project to work on so I decided
    to create a calculator. It was an awful lot harder than I thought -
    looking at the program @{"history" link part7} will tell you that.

    The reason that my previous version 1.0 release of the calculator
    largely didn't work and because of this was released as source code,
    was that I simply hadn't realised how complex the workings of a
    calculator really are. I am still learning.

    As you will notice if you run the calculator, it now has some extra
    functions. I have hoped from the beginning that functions such as
    square, square root and pi could be added. Other functions,
    e.g. sine, cosine, tangent, brackets, etc. are coming soon.


                        @{"Return to contents" link main}
@endnode

